# {% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %} URLÂ in On-demand access flows

On-demand access flows for Service Now and Slack, as well as any custom
flows that include
{% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %}
components, need to be updated due to internal infrastructure changes.

## When did this change take place?

July 7, 2024

## What changed?

The
{% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %}
URL changed from

::: code
    {tenant_name}-sca.cyberark.cloud
:::

to

::: code
    {tenant_name}.sca.cyberark.cloud
:::

## What you need to do

{% $cc_product_vars.Flows-short %}
flows for
{% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %}
that were downloaded and configured before July 7, 2024 need to be
updated. This includes flows for ServiceNow or Slack integrations, as
well as any custom flows you have built.

::: important
[To prevent degradation in
{% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %}
functionality, you must update the
{% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %}
URL by August 31, 2024.]{.Emphasis}

After this date, if your
{% $cc_product_vars.Flows-short %}
flows still have the original configuration:

- {% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %}
  will no longer send email notifications when users request access

<!-- -->

- {% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %}
  will no longer create policy for approved requests

- {% $cc_product_vars.SCA-short %}
  will no longer send email notification for approved or denied requests
:::

